  year               = {2025},
  abstract           = {This paper presents the Graph Engine Service (GES), an advanced graph database management system characterized by its composable architecture and highly factorized query executor. This design enables GES to manage a substantial volume of concurrent queries with remarkable efficiency. GES currently holds the top position in the authoritative LDBC-SNB-DECLARATIVE benchmark rankings, showcasing its superior performance - exceeding the throughput of the second-place system by over three orders of magnitude, which provides its customers with exceptional cost-effectiveness and extraordinary user experiences.},
